quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  7,1,Alif Lām Mīm Sād
  7,2,"This is a Book that has been sent down to you [O Prophet], so do not let your heart be troubled by it; so that you may warn thereby and as a reminder to the believers"
  7,3,"Follow [O mankind] what has been sent down to you from your Lord, and do not follow any guardians besides Him. Little it is that you take heed"
  7,4,"How many towns We have destroyed, and Our punishment came upon them at night or while they were taking midday rest"
  7,5,"Their only cry, when Our punishment came upon them, was, “We were indeed wrongdoers.”"
  7,6,"So We will surely question those to whom the messengers were sent, and We will surely question the messengers themselves"
  7,7,"Then We will surely give them full account [of their deeds] on the basis of knowledge, for We were never absent"
  7,8,"The weighing [of deeds] on that Day will be true and just. Those whose scales [of good deeds] are heavy, it is they who will be the successful"
  7,9,"But those whose scales are light, it is they who have lost their own souls, because they wrongfully rejected Our verses"
  7,10,We established you on earth and provided you with means of livelihood therein. Little do you give thanks
  7,11,"We surely created you, then shaped you, then We said to the angels, “Prostrate before Adam,” so they prostrated, except Iblīs [Satan], who was not one of those who prostrated"
  7,12,"Allah said, “What prevented you from prostrating when I ordered you?” He said, “I am better than him; You created me from fire and created him from clay.”"
  7,13,"Allah said, “Then get down from here! It is not for you to show arrogance here. Get out, for you are one of the disgraced.”"
  7,14,"He said, “Grant me respite until the Day they are resurrected.”"
  7,15,"Allah said, “You are of those who are granted respite’’"
  7,16,"He said, “Since You have led me astray, I will certainly lie in wait for them on Your straight path"
  7,17,"Then I will come against them from their front and from their back, from their right and from their left, and You will not find most of them grateful.”"
  7,18,"Allah said, “Get out of here, disgraced and expelled! I will certainly fill Hell with you and those who follow you all together.”"
  7,19,"“O Adam, dwell in Paradise, you and your wife, and eat from wherever you wish, but do not approach this tree, or else you will both be among the wrongdoers.”"
  7,20,"Then Satan whispered to them in order to expose what was hidden from them of their private parts. He said, “Your Lord has only forbidden to you this tree to prevent you from becoming angels or immortals.”"
  7,21,"And he swore to them, “I am indeed your sincere adviser.”"
  7,22,"So he deluded them both with deception. When they tasted the tree, their private parts became visible to them, so they began to put together leaves of the Garden to cover themselves. Their Lord called them, “Did I not forbid you from that tree and tell you that Satan is your sworn enemy?”"
  7,23,"They said, “Our Lord, we have wronged ourselves; if You do not forgive us and have mercy upon us, we will surely be among the losers.”"
  7,24,"Allah said, “Get down as enemies to one another. You will find a dwelling place on earth and provision for an appointed time.”"
  7,25,"He said, “There you will live, and there you will die, and from there you will be raised again.”"
  7,26,"O children of Adam, We have given you garments that cover your private parts and as an adornment. However, the garment of piety is best. That is one of the signs of Allah, so that they may take heed"
  7,27,"O children of Adam, do not let Satan seduce you as he caused your parents to be expelled from the Garden, stripping them of their garments and making their private parts visible to them. He and his offspring see you from where you cannot see them. We have made the devils allies to those who disbelieve"
  7,28,"When they commit a shameful act, they say, “We found our forefathers doing it, and Allah has enjoined it upon us.” Say, “Allah never enjoins shameful acts. Do you say about Allah something of which you have no knowledge?”"
  7,29,"Say [O Prophet], “My Lord has enjoined doing what is right; direct your faces [to Him alone] wherever you pray; call upon Him with sincere devotion to Him. Just as He created you first, so you will be brought back to life.”"
  7,30,"A group He has guided, and another group deserved to go stray. They have taken devils as their guardians instead of Allah, thinking that they are guided"